    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until later</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and finely dice your <strong>red\u00a0onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (or finely chop) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>red\u00a0chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil\u00a0</strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced red</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once\u00a0slightly softened, add the <strong>grated\u00a0ginger &\u00a0garlic</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min or until\u00a0fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the garlic and ginger are cooking, chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> and <strong>vegetable\u00a0stock mix</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your\u00a0<strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>ground\u00a0turmeric</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the onion\u00a0and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, most of the <strong>chopped\u00a0chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)\u00a0and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for a further 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until starting to thicken \u2013 this is your<strong> Goan-style</strong> <strong>curry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then chop it roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped spinach</strong> to the curry sauce and stir continuously for 1-2 min or until wilted</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the spinach is wilting, cut your <strong>hake fillet[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped hake </strong>to the curry and cook, covered, for 6-7 min or until cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong> Goan-style hake & spinach curry</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely,<strong> </strong>including the stalks, then stir it through the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>coriander rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goan-style-hake-and-spinach-curry-with-coriander-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> Goan-style hake & spinach curry</strong> over the <strong>coriander\u00a0rice</strong> and garnish with the\u00a0<strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped\u00a0chilli\u00a0</strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
